<item>
            <title>[LU-1903] Disable lfsck for ZFS tests</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1903</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0af4d2e2-f9b4-11e1-b8d8-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0af4d2e2-f9b4-11e1-b8d8-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The lfsck.sh test is trying to run against a ZFS-backed OST.  lfsck.sh should be skipped entirely if either the OST or MDT is using ZFS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;e2fsck -d -v -t -t -f -n --mdsdb mdsdb --ostdb ostdb-0 lustre-ost1/ost1
e2fsck 1.42.3.wc3 (15-Aug-2012)
e2fsck: No such file or directory while trying to open lustre-ost1/ost1
Possibly non-existent device?
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
